Command.Name: listAllPluginsInRegistry
Command.Description: Prints out a list of all the plugins currently in the plugin registry.

Command.Name: listAllPluginsInRegistryPath
Command.Description: List all the plugins in the plugins registry path.

Command.Name: countPluginsInRegistry
Command.Description: Print out the number of plugins currently in the plugin registry.

Command.Name: countPluginsInRegistryPath
Command.Description: Print out the number of plugins currently in the plugin registry folder path.

Command.Name: registerPlugin
Command.Description: Add a plugin and its path to the plugin registry for auto-loading.

Command.Name: unregisterPlugin
Command.Description: Remove a named plugin from the plugin registry to prevent auto-loading.

Command.Name: syncPluginRegistryWithPath
Command.Description: Synchronize the plugin registry with the plugins listed in the plugins registry folder path.

Command.Name: unregisterAllPlugins
Command.Description: Unregister all plugins from the plugin registry, clear the plugin registry of all data.

Command.Name: savePluginRegistryToDisk
Command.Description: Save or persist the plugin registry to the hard drive.

Command.Name: loadPlugin
Command.Description: Load a plugin from a specified path.

Command.Name: loadPlugins
Command.Description: Load an array of plugins from a single path or an array of paths.

Command.Name: loadPluginsFromRegistry
Command.Description: Load all the plugins listed in the plugin registry.
